INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (1,1,'Mr WordPress','','https://wordpress.org/','','2015-05-12 01:43:49','2015-05-12 01:43:49','Hi, this is a comment.\nTo delete a comment, just log in and view the post&#039;s comments. There you will have the option to edit or delete them.',0,'post-trashed','','',0,0),(2,27,'deepgreenphilly','starspray21@hotmail.com','http://deepgreenphilly.wordpress.com','71.185.13.83','2015-04-12 08:50:43','2015-04-12 12:50:43','I think this is great. It casts a really wide net and makes the organization seem very welcoming',0,'1','','',0,0),(3,28,'lauracky','lcofsky@gmail.com','http://lauracky.wordpress.com','69.253.127.144','2015-04-14 15:25:08','2015-04-14 19:25:08','I couldn\'t add this myself since I\'m still not an admin, but you might want to include this blog post: http://www.greenphillyblog.com/energy/clean-energy-best-pa-wind-renewable/\n\nIt lists options for people who want to get their electricity from wind power. Once my admin account is set up, I\'d also be happy to include this in a blog post.',0,'1','','',0,0),(4,29,'Dave Moscatello','dkmoscatello@verizon.net','','72.92.1.87','2015-04-11 10:21:52','2015-04-11 14:21:52','This link to the Frebruary article \"Oil-train accidents raise fears in Phila.\" could substitute for the WSJ article:    http://articles.philly.com/2015-02-23/news/59390938_1_oil-trains-open-records-plans',0,'1','','',0,0),(5,29,'mtairygal','meenal.raval@gmail.com','http://www.phillyew.com','68.82.196.237','2015-04-11 10:52:57','2015-04-11 14:52:57','Great. Thanks. Replaced.',0,'1','','',4,0),(6,29,'deepgreenphilly','starspray21@hotmail.com','http://deepgreenphilly.wordpress.com','71.185.13.83','2015-04-12 08:46:33','2015-04-12 12:46:33','I don\'t think the beginning sentence of the first paragraph is a true statement, and it bothers me. Is it really necessary?',0,'1','','',0,0),(7,31,'dimitrovna','tamclements@gmail.com','http://nolackofhatingfrack.wordpress.com','71.224.196.210','2015-04-09 02:08:22','2015-04-09 02:08:22','very nicely focused Meenal. tam',0,'1','','',0,0),(8,31,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-04-09 18:07:06','2015-04-09 22:07:06','It took me awhile to figure out that clicking on the little red hexagon would bring up the menu bar. Can we make the hexagons more obvious?',0,'1','','',0,0),(9,31,'mtairygal','meenal.raval@gmail.com','http://www.phillyew.com','98.115.127.75','2015-04-10 07:46:28','2015-04-10 11:46:28','I hear you, Susan. We do need to change the theme. -Meenal',0,'1','','',8,0),(10,31,'frickrobert','frick.robert@gmail.com','http://frickrobert.wordpress.com','98.221.41.175','2015-04-10 19:26:37','2015-04-10 23:26:37','Hey how do you start a comment thread? I can\'t see it anywhere. What do you think we should do with Resources page? It\'s not visible but I would like people to see the links and offer feedback. I\'ve incorporated additional links on the Policy and Get Involved pages, but we may want to find a better home. We\'ll see by next Wed I guess. \n\nAlso, I made some comments in the copy (visible in a preview) with my initials, in case you came across any.',0,'1','','',9,0),(11,31,'mtairygal','meenal.raval@gmail.com','http://www.phillyew.com','98.115.127.75','2015-04-10 19:46:45','2015-04-10 23:46:45','We need an Action page.',0,'1','','',0,0),(12,31,'mtairygal','meenal.raval@gmail.com','http://www.phillyew.com','98.115.127.75','2015-04-11 08:36:30','2015-04-11 12:36:30','We have an action page...https://pesphl.wordpress.com/2015/04/11/actions-what-you-can-do/',0,'1','','',11,0),(13,31,'Andrew Bowers','bowersad@gmail.com','http://latenightlibrary.wordpress.com/','98.225.174.134','2015-04-12 14:11:58','2015-04-12 18:11:58','I am working on a design for this site',0,'1','','',9,0),(14,31,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-04-13 13:51:13','2015-04-13 17:51:13','We need to make sure it is easy to navigate to all our public pages. For example, the only way to get to the list of who is in the coalition is via a  link on the Who We Are Page, but I think it\'s important enough to be in the menu. Or will there eventually be a site map?  I\'d like whoever ends up designing the architecture to make sure that there are multiple logical paths to each page, not just one. Once again I am arguing for enough redundancy to make the site really robust and welcoming, even if someone only visits a few pages.',0,'1','','',0,0),(15,31,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','http://deleted','71.162.132.202','2015-04-13 13:56:08','2015-04-13 17:56:08','On a second and separate subject, once we go live it would be great to make sure we have as many links to as many other (genuinely relevant) sites as possible on our links page. We can prioritize the links that are more relevant or better in our judgement, but the more links, the easier it is for the spiders to find us.',0,'1','','',0,0),(17,70,'lauracky','lcofsky@gmail.com','http://lauracky.wordpress.com','69.253.127.144','2015-04-14 15:29:03','2015-04-14 19:29:03','My two cents: in the top heading, we should nix \"not corporate rule.\" The reason I say this is because the second part gives the section a negative, contrarian spin. We\'re a positive group!',0,'1','','',0,0),(18,72,'lauracky','lcofsky@gmail.com','http://lauracky.wordpress.com','69.253.127.144','2015-04-14 15:33:22','2015-04-14 19:33:22','This page still needs an anchor.',0,'1','','',0,0),(19,74,'lauracky','lcofsky@gmail.com','http://lauracky.wordpress.com','69.253.127.144','2015-04-14 15:35:00','2015-04-14 19:35:00','Here\'s a thought: could we just change it to \"the three E\'s?\" Would that make sense? We could keep educate, empower, and encourage, and just beef up those three sections.',0,'1','','',0,0),(20,154,'lauracky','lcofsky@gmail.com','http://lauracky.wordpress.com','69.253.127.144','2015-04-14 15:23:01','2015-04-14 19:23:01','This looks good. The one comment I have is that Judy\'s article might be better suited for a different section, since it\'s not necessarily an \"action.\"',0,'1','','',0,0),(21,154,'mtairygal','meenal.raval@gmail.com','http://www.phillyew.com','68.82.196.237','2015-04-14 16:24:58','2015-04-14 20:24:58','At the end of Judy\'s blog post, there\'s an action to reach out to Phila City Council.',0,'1','','',0,0),(22,74,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-13 18:47:10','2015-05-13 18:47:10','Great idea, Laura. Here is the revised text.\r\n\r\nEDUCATE you about what is at stake, the science, economics and politics of clean energy vs. fossil fuels,\r\nEMPOWER you to take practical steps now to conserve energy, save money &amp; live a healthier life,\r\nENCOURAGE you to get involved and connect with organizations working on neighborhood, city-wide or national levels to bring about people-powered change.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.59.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.9 Safari/534.59.10','',0,0),(23,72,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-13 18:48:39','2015-05-13 18:48:39','The link to the What is the FF Hub doesn\'t work.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.59.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.9 Safari/534.59.10','',0,0),(24,70,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-13 18:53:00','2015-05-13 18:53:00','Could be \"People Power, Local Control\" \r\nAlso we will eventually have to change \"Peoples Energy Solutions\" wherever we have it to the name of the Coalition (when we have it, and may it be soon!)',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.59.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.9 Safari/534.59.10','',0,0),(25,246,'Andrew','bowersad@gmail.com','','166.137.244.52','2015-05-13 20:19:05','2015-05-13 20:19:05','Nice post Mt Airy Gal. I would remove the picture at the top however.  The featured image ends up showing up twice.',0,'post-trashed','Mozilla/5.0 (Android; Mobile; rv:38.0) Gecko/38.0 Firefox/38.0','',0,0),(26,246,'Andrew','bowersad@gmail.com','','166.137.244.52','2015-05-13 20:21:40','2015-05-13 20:21:40','Nice Mt Airy Gal! I would remove the picture at the top however.  The featured image ends up showing up twice.',0,'post-trashed','Mozilla/5.0 (Android; Mobile; rv:38.0) Gecko/38.0 Firefox/38.0','',0,0),(27,246,'What&#039;s the Deal with Jim Kenney &amp; Phil Rinaldi?','','http://www.greenphillyblog.com/news/whats-the-deal-with-jim-kenney-phil-rinaldi/','199.195.146.189','2015-05-14 16:01:01','2015-05-14 16:01:01','[&#8230;] Read the full story on the Bright Philly Future website. [&#8230;]',0,'post-trashed','The Incutio XML-RPC PHP Library -- WordPress/4.2.2','pingback',0,0),(28,246,'mtairygal','meenal.raval@gmail.com','','68.82.196.237','2015-05-14 16:42:31','2015-05-14 16:42:31','Good point Andrew. Done.',0,'post-trashed','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_10_3) AppleWebKit/600.5.17 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/8.0.5 Safari/600.5.17','',0,2),(29,27,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-15 14:43:01','2015-05-15 18:43:01','Here\'s a very shortened version of the call. I think it\'s just as comprehensive but more concise:\r\n\r\nWhere does your passion for social and environmental justice lead you?\r\nIf you can answer Yes to any of these, you’re needed on our team!\r\n\r\nAre you an activist who can participate in neighborhood or city-wide events, show up, canvass, make calls, involve your  neighborhood organization, faith community, student or civic group?\r\nAre you a green energy or conservation professional or business owner with services to offer?\r\nAre you a health or legal professional, a scientist, policy analyst, social media whiz, artist or investor concerned about these issues and willing to bring your skills to the table?\r\n\r\nDid we miss anything? Just let us know and we will be happy to talk with you about it.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_9_5) AppleWebKit/600.6.3 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/7.1.6 Safari/537.85.15','',0,0),(30,70,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-15 14:44:47','2015-05-15 18:44:47','If we are our own organization then we can just change Peoples Energy Solutions to Bright Philly Future, wherever it occurs.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_9_5) AppleWebKit/600.6.3 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/7.1.6 Safari/537.85.15','',0,0),(31,29,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-15 14:55:35','2015-05-15 18:55:35','I agree that the sentence could be left out, not because it is untrue (but it depends on your definition of sacrifice, say for example you think life is not worth living without tons of cheap junk from sweatshops in China, but clean air is a useless luxury), but because it makes more sense to say what we are for than what we are not.\r\nAnyhow, here is a shot at rewriting it:\r\n\r\n“Going green” is about transitioning to a healthier, cleaner, more livable city, while growing stable, living wage jobs and opportunities for all, built on proven, readily available, clean energy technologies. In contrast, the dirty fossil fuel “Energy Hub” plan is about turning back the clock to the 19th century, and writing off our city as an environmental “sacrifice zone” for the short-term profit of some of the worst corporate polluters on the planet.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_9_5) AppleWebKit/600.6.3 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/7.1.6 Safari/537.85.15','',0,0),(32,29,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-15 14:58:21','2015-05-15 18:58:21','I would like to see the whole text under \"what is the fossil fuel hub and why do we oppose it\" hidden or on another page so you have to click to see it. Then the \"Resources\" section could be seen without scrolling down to it.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_9_5) AppleWebKit/600.6.3 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/7.1.6 Safari/537.85.15','',0,0),(33,72,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-18 11:09:02','2015-05-18 15:09:02','Alternative language for this page, so we are not speaking prematurely for the Coalition as a whole:\r\n\r\nBright Philly Future grew out of a coalition that came together in response to the news of a December 5, 2014 closed-door conference bringing wealthy investors and representatives of international corporations together to lay plans for turning our city into an “Energy Hub.” This “Energy Hub” would be a receiving, processing and exporting center for some of the most damaging fossil fuel products known. \r\n\r\nWorking together, we realized that we share an alternative vision of Philadelphia as a Clean Energy Hub, a vibrant, dynamic, just and democratic city, a beacon for the 21st century.  The solutions to our many concerns--about jobs, opportunity, public health, clean air and water, and social and economic justice--are right in front of us. \r\n\r\n(Move this from the what we stand for page) \r\nPhiladelphia is home to an abundance of talent, imagination, and proven successes when it comes to sustainability. We know that we have everything we need to be the great city we can be–world class institutions of culture, medicine and higher learning; a diverse and willing workforce; a network of sustainable and ethical businesses ready to grow and invest locally; and countless neighborhood groups, faith communities and civic associations ready to mobilize people to work together for the common good.\r\n\r\nWith your support, we believe Philadelphia can become a beacon for the twenty-first century, turning a city plagued by economic troubles into fertile ground for solutions that work for all.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.59.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.9 Safari/534.59.10','',0,0),(34,68,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-18 11:15:43','2015-05-18 15:15:43','Alternative language for this page:\r\n\r\nBright Philly Future  advocates for investment in our wealth of community-based solutions, rather than corporate deals which cut jobs and put more money in the hands of those who are not invested in the health and well-being of our neighborhoods.\r\n\r\nWe know that people are tired of politics as usual; tired of back-room deals; tired of our voices being ignored; tired of our health and safety being put at risk by polluters; tired of unemployment, underemployment and poverty wage jobs; tired of the “school to prison pipeline” that leaves our youth undereducated, unemployed and swept off the streets and into an out of control system of mass incarceration; and tired of being told that the half-measures and empty promises put on the table by corporate looters are our only choice.\r\n\r\nWe can have more stable, living-wage jobs and shared prosperity without a dirty fossil fuel “energy hub, ” without doubling down on dangerous, explosive trains of fracked shale oil rumbling through our densely populated neighborhoods, and without the toxic air and water pollution that fuel the asthma epidemic that already affects almost one quarter of our children. \r\n\r\nTo learn more about the plan to turn Philadelphia into an environmental sacrifice zone (sometimes referred to as “Houston on the Delaware”) click here (Link to “what is the fossil fuel energy hub and why do we oppose it?”)',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.59.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.9 Safari/534.59.10','',0,0),(35,59,'Susan Saxe','saxesmith@earthlink.net','','71.162.132.202','2015-05-18 11:31:57','2015-05-18 15:31:57','We don\'t need both a Who We Are and an About Us.  I suggest we get rid of About Us and everything under it and just go with Who we are. That solves the mission, vision and goals question, which really belongs to a coalition, not a committee.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.59.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.9 Safari/534.59.10','',0,0);
