s\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:13:\"sample-page-2\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-04-13 01:41:20\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-13 01:41:20\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:34:\"http://www.bowersad.com/?page_id=2\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:13;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:72;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"2\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 01:34:13\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 05:34:13\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:1546:\"Our coalition initially came together in response to the news of a December 5, 2014 closed-door conference bringing wealthy investors and representatives of international corporations together to lay plans for turning our city into an “Energy Hub.” This \"Energy Hub\" would be a receiving, processing and exporting center for some of the most damaging fossil fuel products known. A dirty fossil fuel “energy hub” means doubling down on dangerous, explosive trains of fracked shale oil rumbling through our densely populated neighborhoods, doubling down on toxic air and water pollution and doubling down on asthma and respiratory diseases that already affect almost one quarter of our children and constitute a public health crisis.\n\nTo learn more about the plan to turn Philadelphia into an environmental sacrifice zone (sometimes referred to as “Houston on the Delaware\") click here (<span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">Link to “what is the fossil fuel energy hub and why do we oppose it?”)</span>\n\nWe know that people are tired of politics as usual; tired of back-room deals; tired of our voices being ignored; tired of our health and safety being put at risk by polluters; tired of unemployment, underemployment and poverty wage jobs; tired of the “school to prison pipeline” that leaves our youth undereducated, unemployed and swept off the streets and into an out of control system of mass incarceration; and tired of being told that the half-measures and empty promises put on the table by corporate looters are our only choice.\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:23:\"What brings us together\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:23:\"what-brings-us-together\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 01:34:13\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 05:34:13\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:24;s:4:\"guid\";s:40:\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=72\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"3\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:14;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:70;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"2\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 01:33:55\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 05:33:55\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:3530:\"<h4>PEOPLE POWER, NOT CORPORATE RULE</h4>\nPeople’s Energy Solutions proposes a resilient, green energy plan that puts people, not corporations in charge of our vital natural resources and public infrastructure.\n<h4>INVESTMENT IN PROVEN SLOUTIONS</h4>\nPhiladelphia is home to an abundance of talent, imagination, and proven successes when it comes to sustainability. Hard-working Philadelphians have already laid the groundwork of the imagination for our next era, and the solutions we need are right in front of us. We believe that the key to the future of Philadelphia lies in investment in practical, proven, community-based solutions, rather than corporate deals which cut jobs and exist only to siphon off more wealth into the hands of those who are not invested in the future of our communities.\n<h4>LEADERSHIP FROM THE GROUND UP</h4>\nWith the right leadership, these solutions will work for everybody, improving the health of communities, creating jobs, expanding public services, and turning Philadelphia into a national leader for the twenty-first century. People\'s Energy Solutions is committed to being your guide to these ideas and the organizations who are working to make them reality.\n<h4>TRANSPARENCY</h4>\nWe believe that the future direction of our city should be decided through an open and transparent process, not in closed-door meetings between powerful economic interests and select politicians.\n<h4>DEMOCRACY AND EQUALITY</h4>\nWe believe in an economy that works for everyone, not just a privileged few, a plan that puts equal justice, living wage jobs, clean air and water, and public safety ahead of corporate profits.\n<h4>POLITICAL WILL</h4>\nWe know that the technology already exists to meet our energy needs responsibly, without sacrificing health and safety or contributing to catastrophic climate change, and that the only thing standing in our way is the lack of political will to wholeheartedly embrace a sustainable future. Our purpose is to create that will!\n<h4>COMMUNITY PARTICIPATION</h4>\nWe welcome input from responsible businesses, neighborhood associations, working families, students, senior citizens, and all Philadelphians interested in building a future that is just, sustainable, healthy and secure.\n\n<strong>Gardening\n</strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uG2eHQ9Q078\">Permaculture: A Quiet Revolution\n</a><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/m9y53sa\">About Permaculture\nWhat Your Garden Can Teach About Cities\n</a><a href=\"http://www.appropedia.org/Aquaponics\">About Aquaponics\n</a><a href=\"http://www.richsoil.com/hugelkultur/\">Hugelculture - An Advanced Raised Bed\n</a><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/k76y48w\">New study shows how trees clean the air in London</a>\n\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\n<a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/ou2lnax\">Study of vehicle emissions will aid urban sustainability efforts\n</a><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/oy4gtem\">Inexpensive Electric Cars May Arrive Sooner Than You Think</a>\n\n<strong>Community Capital\n</strong><a href=\"http://timebanks.org/more-about-timebanking/\">Time Banking</a>\n<a href=\"http://ilsr.org/\">Institute for Local Self-Reliance</a><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uG2eHQ9Q078\">\n</a><a href=\"http://transitiontownmedia.org/about-us/what-is-transition-town-media/\">Transition Town (Media, PA)</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.transitionnetwork.org/about\">Transition Network\n</a><a href=\"http://planphilly.com/\">Plan Philly\n</a><a href=\"http://www.phillynn.org/home/default.php\">Philadelphia Neighborhood Networks </a>(RF: Too political?)\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:15:\"What we propose\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:15:\"what-we-propose\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 01:33:55\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 05:33:55\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:24;s:4:\"guid\";s:40:\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=70\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"3\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:15;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:68;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"2\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 01:33:40\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 05:33:40\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:976:\"Peoples Energy Solutions believes that now is the time to ramp up investment in our wealth of community-based solutions, rather than corporate deals which cut jobs and put more money in the hands of those who are not invested in the health and well-being of our neighborhoods.\n\nPhiladelphia is home to an abundance of talent, imagination, and proven successes when it comes to sustainability. We know that we have everything we need to be the great city we can be--world class institutions of culture, medicine and higher learning; a diverse and willing workforce; a network of sustainable and ethical businesses ready to grow and invest locally; and countless neighborhood groups, faith communities and civic associations ready to mobilize people to work together for the common good.\n\nWith your support, we believe Philadelphia can become a beacon for the twenty-first century, turning a city plagued by economic troubles into fertile ground for solutions that work for all.\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:17:\"What we stand for\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:17:\"what-we-stand-for\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 01:33:40\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-09 05:33:40\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:24;s:4:\"guid\";s:40:\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=68\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"1\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:16;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:24;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"2\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2015-04-08 20:00:29\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-08 20:00:29\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:1017:\"<h4>Turning Point Philadelphia - Which path will we take? (need graphic of two alternatives, dirty fossil or clean renewable city)</h4>\nPeople\'s Energy Solutions is the arm of [INSERT Coalition name when we have it] that focuses on practical paths that can be taken to build our city and region into a clean, just and thriving center of commerce, culture and engaged citizenship. For a list of participating organizations, associations and businesses, <a href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/our-coalition/%20\">click here</a>.\n\n[TEXT BELOW ADDED by Meenal.]\n\nDon\'t see your organization? <a href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/get-involved/\">Let us know</a>. We\'d love to have you on board.\n<h4>Our team</h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>Andrew Bowers</li>\n	<li>Dave Moscatello</li>\n	<li>Duncan Wright</li>\n	<li>Laura Cofsky</li>\n	<li>Max Zahniser</li>\n	<li>Meenal Raval</li>\n	<li>Meg Lemieur</li>\n	<li>Mitch Chanin</li>\n	<li>Tamara Clements</li>\n	<li>Rob Frick</li>\n	<li>Ron Whyte</li>\n	<li>Sherry Zhao</li>\n	<li>Susan Saxe</li>\n</ul>\n--\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:10:\"Who We Are\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:5:\"about\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-04-08 20:00:29\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-04-08 20:00:29\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:38:\"http://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=1\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}}s:4:\"cats\";a:10:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":15:{s:7:\"term_id\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"name\";s:6:\"Action\";s:4:\"slug\";s:6:\"action\";s:10:\"term_group\";s:1:\"0\";s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";s:1:\"2\";s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:8:\"category\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"count\";s:1:\"3\";s:6:\"cat_ID\";R:430;s:14:\"category_count\";R:438;s:20:\"category_description\";R:436;s:8:\"cat_name\";R:431;s:17:\"category_nicename\";R:432;s:15:\"category_parent\";R:437;}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":15:{s:7:\"term_id\";s:1:\"3\";s:4:\"name\";s:8:\"Featured\";s:4:\"slug\";s:8:\"featured\";s:10:\"term_group\";s:1:\"0\";s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";s:1:\"3\