INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2015-05-12 01:43:49','2015-05-12 01:43:49','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world','','','2015-05-12 01:58:16','2015-05-12 01:58:16','',0,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2015-05-12 01:43:49','2015-05-12 01:43:49','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2015-05-12 01:43:49','2015-05-12 01:43:49','',0,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(9,1,'2015-04-14 02:39:59','2015-04-14 02:39:59','','kids','','inherit','open','open','','kids','','','2015-04-14 02:39:59','2015-04-14 02:39:59','',0,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/kids.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(11,1,'2015-04-14 02:48:20','2015-04-14 02:48:20','','solar_powered_car','','inherit','open','open','','solar_powered_car','','','2015-04-14 02:48:20','2015-04-14 02:48:20','',0,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/solar_powered_car.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(13,1,'2015-04-14 02:52:45','2015-04-14 02:52:45','Paine Park','Shred!','','trash','open','open','','shred','','','2015-04-14 02:52:45','2015-04-14 02:52:45','',0,'http://www.bowersad.com/?p=13',0,'post','',0),(24,2,'2015-04-08 20:00:29','2015-04-08 20:00:29','<h4>Turning Point Philadelphia - Which path will we take? (need graphic of two alternatives, dirty fossil or clean renewable city)</h4>\nPeople\'s Energy Solutions is the arm of [INSERT Coalition name when we have it] that focuses on practical paths that can be taken to build our city and region into a clean, just and thriving center of commerce, culture and engaged citizenship. For a list of participating organizations, associations and businesses, <a href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/our-coalition/%20\">click here</a>.\n\n[TEXT BELOW ADDED by Meenal.]\n\nDon\'t see your organization? <a href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/get-involved/\">Let us know</a>. We\'d love to have you on board.\n<h4>Our team</h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>Andrew Bowers</li>\n	<li>Dave Moscatello</li>\n	<li>Duncan Wright</li>\n	<li>Laura Cofsky</li>\n	<li>Max Zahniser</li>\n	<li>Meenal Raval</li>\n	<li>Meg Lemieur</li>\n	<li>Mitch Chanin</li>\n	<li>Tamara Clements</li>\n	<li>Rob Frick</li>\n	<li>Ron Whyte</li>\n	<li>Sherry Zhao</li>\n	<li>Susan Saxe</li>\n</ul>\n--','Who We Are','','publish','open','open','','about','','','2015-04-08 20:00:29','2015-04-08 20:00:29','',0,'http://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=1',0,'page','',0),(27,2,'2015-04-08 20:03:47','2015-04-08 20:03:47','Where does your passion for social and environmental justice lead you?\n\nIf you can answer Yes to any of these, you\'re needed on our team!\n<ul>\n	<li>Can you show up at hearings, meetings or protests? In person, on the phone, at City Council, in your neighborhood or in the streets?</li>\n	<li>Are you already active in city government or politics?</li>\n	<li>Are you active in a neighborhood organization, faith community, student or civic group?</li>\n	<li>Are you a developer, architect, builder or contractor engaged in green building or innovation?</li>\n	<li>Are you a renewable energy expert or provider?</li>\n	<li>Are you a health professional concerned about the effects of toxic waste on our community?</li>\n	<li>Are you in the legal profession and able to consult on legal strategies or provide legal support for demonstrations?</li>\n	<li>Are you an activist investor interested in helping move money out of fossil fuels and into green technologies?</li>\n	<li>Are you an artist or graphic designer?</li>\n	<li>Are you a quiet but persistent Fact-Checker?</li>\n	<li>Are you a Facebook or Twitter whiz?</li>\n	<li>Can you do some Web Programming?</li>\n	<li>Are you a health professional?</li>\n	<li>Are you in the legal field?</li>\n	<li>Are you an investor concerned about where your money is going?</li>\n</ul>\nDid we miss anything? Just let us know and we will be happy to talk with you about it.\n\n<strong>CALL US:</strong>  We want to hear how fired up you are! <b>267.338.3459</b>\nA phone conversation will help us explain the current situation and where we need help, and enable us to learn a bit about you and how your skills can be applied towards building alternatives to Big Energy.\n\n<strong>EMAIL US:</strong> Our team of volunteers can be reached by writing to this address: <strong>pes-phl@googlegroups.com</strong>\nOne of us will respond promptly. Do share your phone number with us as well for a timely response.\n\n<strong>FRIEND US:</strong> On Facebook, we\'re <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">PES-PHL</span>  [need to setup]\n\n<strong>FOLLOW US:</strong> On Twitter, we\'re <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">@pes-phl</span>  [need to setup]\n\n<strong>COME FIND US:</strong> We\'re in the streets and in civic meetings, engaging with candidates, or meeting with the media.  Chances are you already know some of us.  Come to one of these upcoming events for a live connection.  The positive energy, exciting ideas and can-do enthusiasm are palpable. See our <a href=\"https://www.google.com/calendar/embed?src=6n6v236t9qekj76i9ub41iil6c%40group.calendar.google.com&amp;ctz=America/New_York%20\" target=\"_blank\">calendar</a>, and come engage us at one of these events.\n\n<strong>JOIN OUR MAILING LIST</strong> to keep abreast of breaking news and opportunities for action. [suggestion: build up contact list for email address pes-phl@googlegroups.com? ]','Get Involved','','publish','open','open','','get-involved','','','2015-04-08 20:03:47','2015-04-08 20:03:47','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=6',0,'page','',2),(28,2,'2015-04-08 20:04:24','2015-04-08 20:04:24','<h4>Be the Change... in how you use energy</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>conserve energy</li>\r\n	<li>use energy efficiently</li>\r\n	<li>switch to renewable electricity\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86703\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_89815\" class=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.communityenergyinc.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Community Energy</a> - for your home, your business or your school from solar and wind farms in Northeast US</span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86072\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86071\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://theenergy.coop/electricity\" target=\"_blank\">The Energy Co-op</a> - for your home or business, from wind farms in PA or solar installations in Philadelphia </span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86069\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86070\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://ethicalelectric.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Ethical Electric</a> - for your home, from wind or solar farms</span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_85824\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_85823\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://www.greenmountainenergy.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Green Mountain Energy</a> - </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>generate your own renewable electricity\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86041\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86057\" class=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.brighteyesolar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">BrightEye Solar</a> - solar installers based out of Lancaster PA                      </span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_85859\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86040\" class=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.solarcity.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SolarCity</a> - California-based company operating nationally                     </span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_85860\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86039\" class=\"\"><a href=\"https://www.sunedison.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sun Edison</a> - national company with nearby offices in Pennsauken NJ                            </span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86037\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_86038\" class=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.firstsolar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">First Solar</a> - global company based out of Arizona with nearby offices in Bridgewater NJ</span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_83931\" dir=\"ltr\"><span id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_84893\"><a href=\"http://us.sunpower.com/ \" target=\"_blank\">Sun Power</a> - California-based company with nearby offices in Hamilton NJ                      </span></li>\r\n	<li id=\"yui_3_16_0_1_1429635703001_85430\"><a href=\"http://www.vivintsolar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Vivant Solar</a> - Utah based company with nearby offices in Mt Laurel NJ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>eat local food</li>\r\n	<li>think outside the car (walk, bike, transit, car-sharing)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Be the Change... in how you make a living</h4>\r\nEvidence shows that dollar for dollar, investments in energy efficiency, and in wind and solar energy, produce many times more jobs than investments in existing fossil fuel development. See links below to understand that <em>clean energy creates more &amp; better jobs</em>: <em>\r\n</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://thinkprogress.org/climate/2012/03/28/453122/fact-sheet-6-things-you-should-know-about-the-value-of-renewable-energy/\" target=\"_blank\">Six Things You Should Know About the Value of Renewable Energy\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://citizensclimatelobby.org/laser-talks/jobs-fossil-fuels-vs-renewables/\" target=\"_blank\">Jobs - Fossil Fuels vs Renewables\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://cleantechnica.com/2013/03/20/over-3-times-more-green-jobs-per-million-than-fossil-fuel-or-nuclear-jobs/\" target=\"_blank\">Over 3 Times More Green Jobs Per $1 Invested Than Fossil Fuel Or Nuclear Jobs\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.heatisonline.org/contentserver/objecthandlers/index.cfm?ID=4637&amp;Method=Full\" target=\"_blank\">Renewable energy promotes US job growth better than investment in fossil fuels\r\n</a><strong>(RF: Direct source for last?)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLinks to clean energy jobs? Green Jobs Philly? Idealist? Craigslist? Specific companies?\r\n\r\n[Meenal: this doesn\'t say much. OK to remove?] We\'re committed to promoting a cleaner, more sustainable future for the city of Philadelphia. Moreover, we believe in a plan that works for all communities, bringing healthy solutions to large and small businesses, neighborhoods, workers, students, senior citizens, and all Philadelphians interested in a higher quality of living.\r\n\r\n[Meenal: this doesn\'t say much. OK to remove?] On this page, you will find links to information and a diverse network of businesses and organizations with a brighter vision for the future. With your support, we believe Philadelphia can become a beacon for the twenty-first century, turning a city plagued by economic troubles into fertile ground for solutions that work for all.\r\n\r\n[Meenal: rest of this page should be moved to a post on resources or policy]\r\n<h4><strong>RESOURCES\r\nSolar, Batteries and Microgrids</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.energysage.com/solar\">Learn About Solar</a> (Energy Sage SunShot)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SOuyZWqhlNU\">How Photovoltaic (PV) Solar Works\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=96WqrcK2OmM\">How Solar Thermal (Hot Water) Works\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-g49IYTKIkA\">Home Energy Management Systems\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.homeedison.com/\">HomeEdison Battery Backup System</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://phys.org/news/2015-03-solarcity-microgrids-tesla-batteries.html\">Tesla Home Battery System</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Community and Energy Cooperatives</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VG3OMfHNJf4\">Starting a Solar Cooperative\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.geo.coop/\">Grassroots Economic Organizing\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://theenergy.coop/\">The Energy Coop\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://communitypowernetwork.org/\">Community Solar Resource Network\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://city.milwaukee.gov/MilwaukeeShines#.VSVVfbqP14Y\">Milwaukee Shines Solar Program</a> - A model for city solar programs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Sustainability and Energy Efficiency</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.inference.eng.cam.ac.uk/sustainable/book/tex/sewtha.pdf\">Sustainable Energy - without the hot air, David JC MacKay</a> (PDF e-book, 12MB) - A book that objectively and comprehensively sets out the various alternative low-carbon pathways that are open to us in a form that is both highly readable and entertaining.\r\n<em>Energy Efficiency</em> <strong>(RF: Links Needed!)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Available Programs, Financing and Policy</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.energysage.com/market/estimate/enter/\">Instant Solar Estimate Generator</a> (FREE - Energy Sage SunShot)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.nrel.gov/docs/fy12osti/54738.pdf\">The Solarize Guidebook (PDF)</a> - Community guide to collective purchasing of residential PV systems (SunShot Program)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.phila.gov/green//index.html\">Philadelphia Greenworks Plan\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.puc.pa.gov/filing_resources/issues_laws_regulations/act_129_information.asp\">PUC Act 129 Information\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.peco.com/Savings/ToolsandCalculators/Pages/default.aspx\">PECO Calculators\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://programs.dsireusa.org/rss/state/44\">DSIRE PA (Complete Program Availability) (RSS Feed)</a> (RF: To be refined)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://programs.dsireusa.org/system/program\">DSIRE Programs (PA filter needed)\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.dsireusa.org/resources/presentations-and-publications/\">DSIRE Presentations and Publications</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Go Renewable','','publish','open','open','','go-renewable','','','2015-05-13 04:02:13','2015-05-13 04:02:13','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=8',0,'page','',1),(29,2,'2015-04-08 20:04:41','2015-04-08 20:04:41','<strong> </strong>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>\"Going green\" is not about sacrifice or austerity, it is about transitioning into a healthier, cleaner, more exciting city, and a new era of opportunities built on the proven power of the people of Philadelphia, using readily available, clean energy technologies.</strong> In contrast, the dirty fossil fuel “Energy Hub” plan is about turning our beloved city into an environmental “sacrifice zone” for the short-term profit of some of the worst corporate polluters on the planet.\n<h3><strong>WHAT IS THE FOSSIL FUEL ENERGY HUB AND WHY DO WE OPPOSE IT?</strong></h3>\nPhil Rinaldi\'s “Energy Hub” plan will introduce more oil pipelines, oil trains, and refineries to Philadelphia. In short, it will re-industrialize Philadelphia.\n\nPhil Rinaldi is the head of Philadelphia Energy Solutions, the corporation responsible for 72% of the toxic air pollution in Philadelphia. For a good summary of what this plan might mean to Philadelphia, check out <a href=\"http://www.gridphilly.com/grid-magazine/2015/2/25/haunted-by-an-industrial-future.html\">Grid Magazine’s expose</a>. Rinaldi’s vision of Philadelphia as an “Energy Hub” is essentially a plan for doubling down on the transport of dirty, dangerous fossil fuel products through Philadelphia in order to process it for sale either domestically or overseas.\n\nThe \"Energy Hub\" is a corporate agenda currently being worked out in secretive meetings that are closed to the public and, for the most part, even the media. While we applaud the city of Philadelphia\'s commitment to sustainability through policies like Greenworks, we strongly oppose Rinaldi\'s plan as undemocratic and a step in the wrong direction for the future of our city.\n\n<strong>THE RISK FROM “OIL BOMB” TRAINS\n</strong>Unbeknownst to many people, Philadelphia already has two or three trains, over a mile long, carrying some of the most volatile fuels known through densely populated neighborhoods every day. These trains consist primarily of outdated tank cars, officially known as <a href=\"http://dot111.info\">DOT111 cars</a>, that were designed for products like corn oil, and were never meant to carry explosive loads. Also known by such colorful names as “rollling pepsi cans,” and  “the Ford Pintos of the rails” these cars are unstable and prone to derail and explode, causing <a href=\"http://www.motherjones.com/environment/2014/05/oil-tank-trains-bakken-crude-accidents\">massive damage and loss of life</a>.\n\nTo make matters worse, these “bomb trains” roll through our city daily, over a crumbling rail infrastructure, and particularly over unsafe, poorly maintained bridges. This has already led to <a href=\"http://ucreview.com/shale-oil-trains-bring-danger-to-philadelphia-p5508-112.htm\">two recent near misses</a>. The industry goes to great lengths to hide the facts about these “oil bomb” trains, but it is very hard to hide when the inevitable happens. See <a href=\"http://articles.philly.com/2015-02-23/news/59390938_1_oil-trains-open-records-plans\" target=\"_blank\">Oil-train accidents raise concern in Phila</a>, in the Feb 23rd 2015 Inquirer.\n\n<strong>PUBLIC HEALTH RISKS\n</strong>The Rinaldi plan also means more pipelines, more pollution-belching factories, more toxic fumes, and more asthma and lung disease in a city already plagued by an <a href=\"http://www.portal.state.pa.us/portal/server.pt?open=514&amp;objID=557612&amp;mode=2\">epidemic of these ailments</a>.\n\nThe Energy Hub not only represents a public health risk to Philadelphia. The means of obtaining the toxic gas and oil that will flow through our area also poses a risk to people who live in “fracking country,” our fellow Pennsylvanians and people from other states.<a href=\"http://www.lwvny.org/advocacy/issues/2011/HydraulicFracturing_060211.pdf\">\nLWVNY: Public Hearing on the Health Impacts of Hydraulic Fracturing Techniques (PDF)</a>\n\n<strong>HOW ABOUT PIPELINES?\n</strong>Despite the proven health risks, pipelines are touted as a “safer” way to move gas and oil, but to some, pipelines are just a way of hiding the danger underground. What constitutes “safe” to the industry is not always what the actual human beings in the path of these pipelines might consider safe. The danger is to our entire region, not just Philadelphia.\n<a href=\"http://articles.philly.com/2015-02-02/business/58679883_1_pipeline-route-pipeline-company-pipeline-fight\">Opposition greets proposed Marcellus Shale-Trenton pipeline</a>\n\n<strong>CLIMATE IMPACTS\n</strong>Another important thing to know about Phillip Rinaldi is that he is on record as a climate denier, as explicitly stated in a February 6, 2015 interview with Philadelphia Business Journal\n\n<strong><em>PBJ</em></strong><em>: Some people say we should take advantage of the natural gas resource to get to renewables. Others say we should just invest fully in renewables. What\'s your view on either of those?</em>\n\n<strong><em>PR</em></strong><em>: This is America, people are entitled to their views no matter how idiotic they are. And they are idiotic indeed. … It\'s driven by crazy science. Someone who said that we\'re killing the world and \'gee, if you would only stop burning carbon, the world won\'t die.\' I don\'t think there\'s any evidence that that\'s the case. I don\'t think it\'s very practical. </em><a href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/morning_roundup/2015/02/q-a-with-phil-rinaldi-on-philadelphia-as-an-energy.html?page=all\">View Full Interview</a>\n\nBecome a part of the People\'s Energy Solutions: <a title=\"Get Involved\" href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/get-involved/\">Join the Conversation</a>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h4><strong>RESOURCES</strong>\n<strong>Health Impacts</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/p93falr\">The White House wants to explore how climate change makes you sick</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Policy</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/np777x9\">Switching to 100% renewables by 2050 would save major fossil economies $500 billion\n</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/q2aqkwq\">Solar Panels Or Greenery Required For Every New Building Rooftop In France\n</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/m85cu5s\">Teens\' climate-change suit hits court with call to protect our air</a></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','Policy','','publish','open','open','','policy','','','2015-04-08 20:04:41','2015-04-08 20:04:41','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=10',0,'page','',5),(31,2,'2015-04-08 20:12:59','2015-04-08 20:12:59','<strong>Welcome!</strong>\n\nPeoples Energy Solutions is an action committee of, <strong>(Name TBD)</strong>, a large &amp; growing coalition committed to a just and sustainable future for Philadelphia.\n\nPhiladelphia is home to an abundance of talent, imagination, and proven successes when it comes to sustainability. We know that we have everything we need to be the great city we can be--world class institutions of culture, medicine and higher learning; a diverse and willing workforce; a network of sustainable and ethical businesses ready to grow and invest locally; and countless neighborhood groups, faith communities and civic associations ready to mobilize people to work together for the common good. <del></del>We believe that now is the time to ramp up investment in our wealth of community-based solutions, rather than corporate deals which cut jobs and put more money in the hands of those who are not invested in the health of our neighborhoods.\n\nCheck us out! We\'d love to meet you!\n\n<a title=\"Who We Are\" href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/about/\">Who We Are</a>\nOur mission, vision and goals.\n\n<a title=\"Get Involved\" href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/get-involved/\">Get Involved!</a>\nContribute your passion and skills to create a sustainable Philadelphia.\n\n<a title=\"Go Renewable\" href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/go-renewable/\">Go Renewable</a>\nLearn how to go renewable and stop the flow of money to groups who do not have your interests in mind.\n\n<a title=\"Policy\" href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/policy/\">Policy </a>\nLearn about the proposed \'Energy Hub\' and how it would affect your community.\n\n<a title=\"Blog\" href=\"https://pesphl.wordpress.com/blog/\">Blog</a> <strong>(TBD: RSS News, Inspiration, etc...)</strong>\nJoin the conversation!\n\nEvents (link to Google Calendar or Meetup Group, etc.)','Home','','publish','open','open','','home','','','2015-04-08 20:12:59','2015-04-08 20:12:59','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=14',0,'page','',9),(32,2,'2015-04-08 20:18:36','2015-04-08 20:18:36','Shared writings from our various team members','Blog','','publish','open','open','','blog','','','2015-04-08 20:18:36','2015-04-08 20:18:36','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=16',0,'page','',0),(44,2,'2015-04-08 21:51:33','2015-04-08 21:51:33','Despite reading, learning, talking about energy for the past several months, I just stumbled upon this blog post (<a href=\"http://www.greenphillyblog.com/sponsored-post/support-clean-local-energy-hub-choose-pa-wind-2015/\">Support a Clean, Local Energy Hub: Choose PA Wind in 2015</a>) by Julie Hancher of <a href=\"http://www.greenphillyblog.com\">GreenPhillyBlog</a> today.\n<blockquote>\"Yet Philadelphia doesn’t have to be an energy hub for natural gas and fossil fuels to be a powerhouse – we have the potential to be <em>a clean</em> energy hub right here.\"</blockquote>\nFelt it was an appropriate  start for this site. Great meeting you today, Julie, at the #goodeconomyphilly Twitter chat with City Council candidates.','Support a clean, local energy hub','','publish','open','open','','support-a-clean-local-energy-hub','','','2015-05-13 18:35:31','2015-05-13 18:35:31','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?p=44',0,'post','',0),(59,2,'2015-04-09 01:26:50','2015-04-09 05:26:50','Our Mission is to identify and promote practical plans for building a thriving and equitable regional economy that promotes full employment and secure, living-wage jobs while protecting the health and safety of our neighborhoods.  We believe this is best achieved through an open, transparent and deeply democratic process that puts the future of our city in the hands of the people who live and work here, not distant corporations and their political operatives.','Our Mission','','publish','open','closed','','our-mission','','','2015-04-09 01:26:50','2015-04-09 05:26:50','',31,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=59',0,'page','',1),(61,2,'2015-04-09 01:27:04','2015-04-09 05:27:04','We take a bottom-up approach that focuses on building relationships between people with similar goals in order to catalyze self-organization and action. Our goal is to educate the people in their circles to facilitate positive change in their neighborhoods and communities, resulting in carbon neutral (or negative), locally governed, resilient and regenerative communities.','Our Vision','','publish','open','closed','','our-vision','','','2015-04-09 01:27:04','2015-04-09 05:27:04','',31,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=61',0,'page','',0),(63,2,'2015-04-09 01:27:18','2015-04-09 05:27:18','<ol>\n	<li>To provide an educational resource for the public on the developments of the proposed fossil fuel energy hub.</li>\n	<li>To identify and propose solutions for an alternative energy hub centered on renewable, sustainable energy.</li>\n	<li>To make as many people in Greater Philadelphia aware of the immediate health, safety and economic impacts of a fossil fuel energy hub as possible, and to build popular support for responsible, sustainable and economically just alternatives.</li>\n</ol>','Our Goals','','publish','open','closed','','our-goals','','','2015-04-09 01:27:18','2015-04-09 05:27:18','',31,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=63',0,'page','',0),(68,2,'2015-04-09 01:33:40','2015-04-09 05:33:40','Peoples Energy Solutions believes that now is the time to ramp up investment in our wealth of community-based solutions, rather than corporate deals which cut jobs and put more money in the hands of those who are not invested in the health and well-being of our neighborhoods.\n\nPhiladelphia is home to an abundance of talent, imagination, and proven successes when it comes to sustainability. We know that we have everything we need to be the great city we can be--world class institutions of culture, medicine and higher learning; a diverse and willing workforce; a network of sustainable and ethical businesses ready to grow and invest locally; and countless neighborhood groups, faith communities and civic associations ready to mobilize people to work together for the common good.\n\nWith your support, we believe Philadelphia can become a beacon for the twenty-first century, turning a city plagued by economic troubles into fertile ground for solutions that work for all.','What we stand for','','publish','open','closed','','what-we-stand-for','','','2015-04-09 01:33:40','2015-04-09 05:33:40','',24,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=68',0,'page','',1),(70,2,'2015-04-09 01:33:55','2015-04-09 05:33:55','<h4>PEOPLE POWER, NOT CORPORATE RULE</h4>\nPeople’s Energy Solutions proposes a resilient, green energy plan that puts people, not corporations in charge of our vital natural resources and public infrastructure.\n<h4>INVESTMENT IN PROVEN SLOUTIONS</h4>\nPhiladelphia is home to an abundance of talent, imagination, and proven successes when it comes to sustainability. Hard-working Philadelphians have already laid the groundwork of the imagination for our next era, and the solutions we need are right in front of us. We believe that the key to the future of Philadelphia lies in investment in practical, proven, community-based solutions, rather than corporate deals which cut jobs and exist only to siphon off more wealth into the hands of those who are not invested in the future of our communities.\n<h4>LEADERSHIP FROM THE GROUND UP</h4>\nWith the right leadership, these solutions will work for everybody, improving the health of communities, creating jobs, expanding public services, and turning Philadelphia into a national leader for the twenty-first century. People\'s Energy Solutions is committed to being your guide to these ideas and the organizations who are working to make them reality.\n<h4>TRANSPARENCY</h4>\nWe believe that the future direction of our city should be decided through an open and transparent process, not in closed-door meetings between powerful economic interests and select politicians.\n<h4>DEMOCRACY AND EQUALITY</h4>\nWe believe in an economy that works for everyone, not just a privileged few, a plan that puts equal justice, living wage jobs, clean air and water, and public safety ahead of corporate profits.\n<h4>POLITICAL WILL</h4>\nWe know that the technology already exists to meet our energy needs responsibly, without sacrificing health and safety or contributing to catastrophic climate change, and that the only thing standing in our way is the lack of political will to wholeheartedly embrace a sustainable future. Our purpose is to create that will!\n<h4>COMMUNITY PARTICIPATION</h4>\nWe welcome input from responsible businesses, neighborhood associations, working families, students, senior citizens, and all Philadelphians interested in building a future that is just, sustainable, healthy and secure.\n\n<strong>Gardening\n</strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uG2eHQ9Q078\">Permaculture: A Quiet Revolution\n</a><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/m9y53sa\">About Permaculture\nWhat Your Garden Can Teach About Cities\n</a><a href=\"http://www.appropedia.org/Aquaponics\">About Aquaponics\n</a><a href=\"http://www.richsoil.com/hugelkultur/\">Hugelculture - An Advanced Raised Bed\n</a><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/k76y48w\">New study shows how trees clean the air in London</a>\n\n<strong>Transportation</strong>\n<a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/ou2lnax\">Study of vehicle emissions will aid urban sustainability efforts\n</a><a href=\"http://tinyurl.com/oy4gtem\">Inexpensive Electric Cars May Arrive Sooner Than You Think</a>\n\n<strong>Community Capital\n</strong><a href=\"http://timebanks.org/more-about-timebanking/\">Time Banking</a>\n<a href=\"http://ilsr.org/\">Institute for Local Self-Reliance</a><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uG2eHQ9Q078\">\n</a><a href=\"http://transitiontownmedia.org/about-us/what-is-transition-town-media/\">Transition Town (Media, PA)</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.transitionnetwork.org/about\">Transition Network\n</a><a href=\"http://planphilly.com/\">Plan Philly\n</a><a href=\"http://www.phillynn.org/home/default.php\">Philadelphia Neighborhood Networks </a>(RF: Too political?)','What we propose','','publish','open','closed','','what-we-propose','','','2015-04-09 01:33:55','2015-04-09 05:33:55','',24,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=70',0,'page','',3),(72,2,'2015-04-09 01:34:13','2015-04-09 05:34:13','Our coalition initially came together in response to the news of a December 5, 2014 closed-door conference bringing wealthy investors and representatives of international corporations together to lay plans for turning our city into an “Energy Hub.” This \"Energy Hub\" would be a receiving, processing and exporting center for some of the most damaging fossil fuel products known. A dirty fossil fuel “energy hub” means doubling down on dangerous, explosive trains of fracked shale oil rumbling through our densely populated neighborhoods, doubling down on toxic air and water pollution and doubling down on asthma and respiratory diseases that already affect almost one quarter of our children and constitute a public health crisis.\n\nTo learn more about the plan to turn Philadelphia into an environmental sacrifice zone (sometimes referred to as “Houston on the Delaware\") click here (<span style=\"color:#0000ff;\">Link to “what is the fossil fuel energy hub and why do we oppose it?”)</span>\n\nWe know that people are tired of politics as usual; tired of back-room deals; tired of our voices being ignored; tired of our health and safety being put at risk by polluters; tired of unemployment, underemployment and poverty wage jobs; tired of the “school to prison pipeline” that leaves our youth undereducated, unemployed and swept off the streets and into an out of control system of mass incarceration; and tired of being told that the half-measures and empty promises put on the table by corporate looters are our only choice.','What brings us together','','publish','open','closed','','what-brings-us-together','','','2015-04-09 01:34:13','2015-04-09 05:34:13','',24,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=72',0,'page','',3),(74,2,'2015-04-09 01:34:32','2015-04-09 01:34:32','Our purpose is to:\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\"><strong>INFORM</strong> you about what is at stake,\n<strong>EDUCATE</strong> you about the science, economics and politics of clean energy vs. fossil fuels,\n<strong>EMPOWER</strong> you to take practical steps now to conserve energy, save money &amp; live a healthier life,\n<strong>CONNECT</strong> you with organizations working on neighborhood, citywide or national levels to bring about people-powered change,\n<strong>INSPIRE</strong> you with hope, and\n<strong>ENCOURAGE</strong> you to get involved.</p>','Our purpose','','publish','open','open','','our-purpose','','','2015-04-09 01:34:32','2015-04-09 01:34:32','',24,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=74',0,'page','',2),(95,3,'2015-04-09 03:38:15','2015-04-09 03:38:15','','Resources','','publish','open','open','','resources','','','2015-04-09 03:38:15','2015-04-09 03:38:15','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=95',0,'page','',0),(110,2,'2015-04-09 13:20:43','2015-04-09 17:20:43','These are the organizations that make up our coalition, which is fighting against the proposed dirty energy hub, and for a just, green and democratic Philadelphia:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://350philly.weebly.com/\" target=\"_blank\">350 Philadelphia</a></li>\r\n	<li>Beehive Collective in Kensington</li>\r\n	<li>Be the Change, Philadelphia chapter</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://calltothebar.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Call to the Bar</a>, led by Phila attorney Steve Harvey, inviting all attorneys to step up to work on climate change</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://cleanair.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Clean Air Council</a>, founded in 1967, now with 8000 members</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://cleanwateraction.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Clean Water Action</a>, founded in 1972, now with 1,000,000 members</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://delawareriverkeeper.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Delaware Riverkeeper Network</a>, established in 1988</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/edgephilly?fref=ts\" target=\"_blank\">EDGE</a> (Encouraging Development of a Green Economy)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://ecasavesenergy.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Energy Coordinating Agency</a>, founded in the early ’80s</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://foodandwaterwatch.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Food &amp; Water Watch</a>, established in 2005</li>\r\n	<li>Philadelphia chapter of <a href=\"http://paipl.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Pennsylvania Interfaith Power &amp; Light</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://maypopcollective.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Maypop Collective</a> for Climate and Economic Justice</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://momscleanairforce.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Mom’s Clean Air Force</a>, and their naptime activism around climate change, with 410,000 members nationally and over 17,000 members in PA</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://pennenvironment.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Penn Environment</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://phillyew.com/\" target=\"_blank\">PHEW! a bike shop</a>, getting people out of cars and onto bikes since 2009\r\nPhiladephia Jewish Climate Action Network</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://psrphila.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Physicians for Social Responsibility, Philadelphia</a> chapter</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://practicalenergy.net/\" target=\"_blank\">Practical Energy Solutions</a>\r\nPraxis Building Solutions &amp; the Sustainability Nexus at CityCoho</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://protectingourwaters.wordpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Protecting Our Waters</a>, founded in 2009, with over 4000 members</li>\r\n	<li>Sierra Club’s Pennsylvania chapter</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://sbnphiladelphia.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Sustainable Business Network of Greater Philadelphia</a> (SBN)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://transitionphilly.wordpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Transition Philadelphia</a>, inviting all Philadelphians to transition to a low-carbon relocalized economy.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','Our Coalition','','private','open','closed','','our-coalition','','','2015-05-16 11:16:49','2015-05-16 15:16:49','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?page_id=110',0,'page','',0),(154,2,'2015-04-11 07:53:42','2015-04-11 11:53:42','Things to read and sign and share, all written by our team.\r\n\r\nOn 4/6/15, see Judy Wick’s guest post on <a href=\"http://foodandwaterwatch.org\" target=\"_blank\">Food &amp; Water Watch</a>\'s blog titled <a href=\"http://www.foodandwaterwatch.org/blogs/standing-up-for-philadelphias-sustainable-economy/\" target=\"_blank\">Standing up for Philadelphia\'s Sustainable Economy</a>. Judy is the founder of the <a href=\"http://www.whitedog.com\" target=\"_blank\">White Dog Café</a>. She also founded the <a href=\"http://sbnphiladelphia.org\" target=\"_blank\">Sustainable Business Network of Greater Philadelphia</a> and <a href=\"http://fairfoodphilly.org\" target=\"_blank\">Fair Food Philly</a>.\r\n\r\nOn 3/19/15, see <a href=\"https://www.ecasavesenergy.org\" target=\"_blank\">The Energy Coordinating Agency</a>\'s post titled <a href=\"https://www.ecasavesenergy.org/about/eca-news/we-have-plan-will-you-sign\" target=\"_blank\">We have a Plan. Will you Sign on?</a>, which lists the ECA’s <a href=\"https://www.ecasavesenergy.org/ecas-recommendations-next-mayor-philadelphia\" target=\"_blank\">Recommendations for the next Mayor of Philadelphia</a>, offering to \"Unleash The Power Of Energy Efficiency To Grow Philadelphia’s Economy And Create Local Jobs\".\r\n\r\nOn 3/5/15, Sam Bernhardt of Food &amp; Water Watch wrote this petition, titled <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1uHjY5NOPnhad7tNYXoHShD0xyMOvGrLx5k47nH3c_Tk/viewform\" target=\"_blank\">Protect Our Health and Safety From the Dirty Fossil Fuel Barrage!</a>','Actions - What you can do','','publish','open','open','','actions-what-you-can-do','','','2015-05-13 18:22:59','2015-05-13 18:22:59','',0,'https://pesphl.wordpress.com/?p=154',0,'post','',2),(157,1,'2015-04-17 16:02:15','2015-04-17 16:02:15','','take-action','','inherit','open','open','','take-action','','','2015-04-17 16:02:15','2015-04-17 16:02:15','',154,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/take-action-e1429322212796.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(161,1,'2015-04-18 02:15:07','2015-04-18 02:15:07','','36701b830108af8a_640_action','','inherit','open','open','','36701b830108af8a_640_action','','','2015-04-18 02:15:07','2015-04-18 02:15:07','',154,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/36701b830108af8a_640_action-e1429323464628.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(162,1,'2015-04-18 02:15:29','2015-04-18 02:15:29','','36701b830108af8a_640_action1','','inherit','open','open','','36701b830108af8a_640_action1','','','2015-04-18 02:15:29','2015-04-18 02:15:29','',154,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/36701b830108af8a_640_action1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(163,1,'2015-04-18 02:31:05','2015-04-18 02:31:05','','454c2d22228ae53d_150_superhero','','inherit','open','open','','454c2d22228ae53d_150_superhero','','','2015-04-18 02:31:05','2015-04-18 02:31:05','',154,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/454c2d22228ae53d_150_superhero.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(165,1,'2015-04-18 02:31:22','2015-04-18 02:31:22','','454c2d22228ae53d_640_superhero','','inherit','open','open','','454c2d22228ae53d_640_superhero','','','2015-04-18 02:31:22','2015-04-18 02:31:22','',154,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/454c2d22228ae53d_640_superhero.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(167,1,'2015-04-18 02:44:51','2015-04-18 02:44:51','','Solar-Panels-Jun-12-700x463','','inherit','open','open','','solar-panels-jun-12-700x463','','','2015-04-18 02:44:51','2015-04-18 02:44:51','',154,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Solar-Panels-Jun-12-700x463.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(172,2,'2015-04-19 18:42:04','2015-04-19 18:42:04','Philadelphia City Councilman David Oh arranged for an event on the Drexel campus last Thursday. Titled <em>LNG Exports: Exploring the possibilities in Philadelphia</em>, it entailed a keynote presentation by Cheniere Energy, opportunities for the nation &amp; Philadelphia in LNG production &amp; export, plus 3 panels on LNG &amp; energy infrastructure, market analysis &amp; investment, site preparation.\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-175 size-medium aligncenter\" src=\"http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0097-e1429449335795-300x101.jpg\" alt=\"LNG panel\" width=\"300\" height=\"101\" />\n\nHere\'s what we found about <a href=\"http://davidstockmanscontracorner.com/cheniere-energy-poster-boy-for-the-shale-gas-hallucination/\" target=\"_blank\">Cheniere Energy: Poster-boy For The Shale Gas Hallucination</a>, which, summarized, states that \"the shale gas story is not about an economic miracle, the wonders of technology, the prowess of job creators.  Instead, it\'s a place where the cheap capital enabled by central banks goes to die.\"\n\nSeveral residents went, and found that most of the attendees at this forum did not live in our region. That the panelists were likewise from all around the US. That there was no representation from public health professionals, nor any mention of public health.  Who will speak for the people? When citizens began questioning Councilman Oh, the reply was... I don\'t work for you. So the questions, and the attacks, on industry continued. And yes, security was called to protect industry from citizens, and one by one, the citizens were escorted out.\n\nSome of what happened was covered by the media. Jon Hurdle of StateImpactPA wrote <img class=\" wp-image-176 size-thumbnail alignright\" src=\"http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0083-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_0083\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><a href=\"http://stateimpact.npr.org/pennsylvania/2015/04/17/shale-gas-opponents-shout-down-industry-speaker-at-lng-session/\" target=\"_blank\">Shale Gas Opponents Shout Down Industry Speaker at Philadelphia LNG Session</a>; Andrew Maykuth of the Philadelphia Inquirer wrote <a href=\"http://www.philly.com/philly/business/20150417_Anti-drilling_protest_interrupts_Drexel_energy_forum.html\" target=\"_blank\">Anti-drilling protest interrupts Drexel energy forum</a>; and someone from the Marcellus Drilling industry wrote <a href=\"http://marcellusdrilling.com/2015/04/peaceful-protesters-removed-from-lng-export-hearing-in-philly/\" target=\"_blank\">\"Peaceful\" Protesters Removed from LNG Export Hearing in Philly</a>.\n\nI do hope Councilman Oh heard us. And plans to gain a balanced education around this subject by inviting public health professionals and those in the renewable energy field to a future forum.  We, as citizens of greater Philadelphia, have concerns. Concerns about air quality from increased emissions. Concerns about water quality when we hear about a tunnel under the Delaware river. Concerns about pipelines coming through our properties, bringing the Marcellus gas into our region. Concerns about trains exploding from the increased volume of dirty fossil fuels headed our way.\n\nWe invite Councilman Oh, and all of City Council to look to the future. A future with reduced greenhouse gases, a future with solar panels or greenery on every roof, a future with fewer cars and more rapid transit, a bright green future for future generations. We can do it. We must do it.','Disruption at LNG Exports Talk','','publish','open','open','','disruption-at-lng-exports-talk','','','2015-05-13 18:34:28','2015-05-13 18:34:28','',0,'http://brightphillyfuture.bowersad.com/?p=172',0,'post','',0),(175,2,'2015-04-19 13:13:59','2015-04-19 13:13:59','','LNG panel','','inherit','open','open','','img_0097','','','2015-04-19 13:13:59','2015-04-19 13:13:59','',172,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0097-e1429449335795.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(176,2,'2015-04-19 13:17:03','2015-04-19 13:17:03','','IMG_0083','','inherit','open','open','','img_0083','','','2015-04-19 13:17:03','2015-04-19 13:17:03','',172,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/IMG_0083.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(178,2,'2015-04-19 18:42:23','2015-04-19 18:42:23','I first met Rekha last February, when she too trudged in the snow and ice form Northwest Philadelphia into <a href=\"http://citycoho.com\" target=\"_blank\">City Coho</a>, to witness the formation of our coalition.  She returned to <a href=\"http://sch.org\" target=\"_blank\">SCH</a> (Springside Chestnut Hill Academy) and proceeded to organize the upcoming <a href=\"http://www.chestnuthilllocal.com/2015/04/15/sch-academy-student-to-host-girls-climate-summit/\" target=\"_blank\">Girl\'s Climate Summit</a>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_179\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/REL_Climat-Summit.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-179\" src=\"http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/REL_Climat-Summit-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"photo courtesy Chestnut Hill Local\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> photo courtesy Chestnut Hill Local[/caption]\r\n\r\nIn the process, it seems she\'s met some pretty interesting local groups. Like <a href=\"http://fairmountworks.com\" target=\"_blank\">Philadelphia Water Works</a>, the <a href=\"http://ecasavesenergy.org\" target=\"_blank\">Energy Coordinating Agency</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.fi.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Franklin Institute</a>, the Climate &amp; Urban Systems Partnership, <a href=\"http://protectingourwaters.wordpress.com\" target=\"_blank\">Protecting Our Waters</a>, the <a href=\"http://dvgbc.org\" target=\"_blank\">Delaware Valley Green Building Council,</a> as well as the Phila chapter of <a href=\"http://psrphila.org\" target=\"_blank\">Physicians for Social Responsibility</a>.\r\n\r\nFollow her at <a href=\"https://twitter.com/climategirls\" target=\"_blank\">@climategirls</a>!','Meet our young leader: Rekha Dhillon-Richardson','','publish','open','open','','meet-our-young-leader-rekha-dhillon-richardson','','','2015-05-13 18:32:53','2015-05-13 18:32:53','',0,'http://brightphillyfuture.bowersad.com/?p=178',0,'post','',0),(179,2,'2015-04-19 18:39:44','2015-04-19 18:39:44','','REL_Climat-Summit','photo courtesy Chestnut Hill Local','inherit','open','open','','rel_climat-summit','','','2015-04-19 18:39:44','2015-04-19 18:39:44','',178,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/REL_Climat-Summit.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(183,2,'2015-04-20 14:11:24','2015-04-20 14:11:24','Another voice from our coalition. That of Zein Nakhoda, which you can read in it\'s entirety <a href=\"http://215pa.com/energy-future/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. Zein was amongst the several citizens who spoke at the public hearing of Philadelphia City Council\'s Special Committee on Energy Opportunities. Some quotes...\n<blockquote>\"Philadelphia should not build its energy future on fuels that exacerbate environmental and economic disaster.\n\nPhiladelphia should not sacrifice the long term security of residents and workers for the short-term gains of fossil fuel corporations. Nor should it rely on precarious and limited resources such as shale gas – which requires toxic and destructive fracking and transport practices in order to get to Philadelphia.\n\nThe energy transition we need would create living wage “climate jobs” – <strong>green union jobs in renewable energy and energy efficiency sectors that mitigate the pollution in our communities and curb carbon emissions.</strong>\n\nThis transition is possible. For example, a Center for American Progress study found that 2.5 to 4 more jobs are created for each million dollars spent on energy efficiency measures, like retrofitting and mass transit, than jobs from one million dollars spent on oil and natural gas operations.\"</blockquote>','Philadelphia\'s Energy Future','','publish','open','open','','philadelphias-energy-future','','','2015-04-20 14:11:24','2015-04-20 14:11:24','',0,'http://brightphillyfuture.bowersad.com/?p=183',0,'post','',0),(196,1,'2015-04-29 02:29:17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','In what is likely a prelude to an announcement from the Pope in June Cardinal Peter Turkson called for','Vatican official calls for leaders to start awakening to climate science','','draft','open','open','','','','','2015-04-29 02:29:17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://brightphillyfuture.bowersad.com/?p=196',0,'post','',0),(198,1,'2015-05-01 14:37:11','2015-05-01 14:37:11','Great little video posted by <a href=\"http://www.philly.com/philly/news/politics/mayor/Street_Level_Living_with_a_refinery_in_South_Philly.html\" target=\"_blank\">Philly.com</a> with West Passyunk Neighbors Association Jennifer Harrison discussing living next door to the PES oil refinery in South Philadelphia.\r\n\r\nShe details how the monitoring station instructs local residents that they should drive less and consume less energy in order to breath cleaner air.  In a classic blame the victim mentality, the implication would be that the oil refined at PES is emitting vast amounts of particulate emissions each year and we are at fault for that because we drive and use light bulbs.\r\n\r\nOf course the truth is if everyone in Philadelphia stopped driving and using electricity tomorrow the amount of emissions from the refinery wouldn\'t lower by one particle, but we will still have to breath it in.\r\n\r\nThe video closing with Harrison asking the poignant question of how would the next mayor deal with the issues that are arising for people who have to live next door to an energy hub.\r\n\r\nThe article and video are part of a series about \"little things\" around Philly that never get fixed, and they are looking to talk to other leaders of RCO\'s about issues the next mayor should be made aware of.  All things clean air and refinery related would seem like perfect topics, so if you are an RCO or know an RCO have them contact Gregg Gethard at gregg_gethard@yahoo.com or call (215)854-2267.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Living Next Door to an Energy Hub','','publish','open','open','','living-next-door-to-an-energy-hub','','','2015-05-14 02:47:57','2015-05-14 02:47:57','',0,'http://brightphillyfuture.bowersad.com/?p=198',0,'post','',0),(208,1,'2015-05-05 03:34:49','2015-05-05 03:34:49','','About Us','','publish','open','open','','about-us','','','2015-05-05 03:34:49','2015-05-05 03:34:49','',0,'http://brightphillyfuture.bowersad.com/?page_id=208',0,'page','',0),(214,1,'2015-04-13 01:54:17','2015-04-13 01:54:17','Philly.com posted an <a href=\"http://articles.philly.com/2015-04-13/news/61108220_1_largest-oil-refinery-philadelphia-energy-solutions-pollution\">excellent article</a> yesterday which highlights how no-brainer the real choice over the debate about having a refinery within the confines of our city.  Good paying union jobs always sound great, however the price we are paying for them is jaw dropping.\r\n<blockquote>In 2013, according to the latest statistics available from the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency, the site - the largest oil refinery on the East Coast - let loose 701,284 pounds (or more than 350 tons) of hazardous air pollutants, including roughly 29 tons of benzene, a potent carcinogen, and many more tons of other toxins that experts say can contribute to breathing problems such as asthma.</blockquote>\r\nThey also go on to highlight how these raw numbers translate into what happens when you live here.\r\n<blockquote>The continued pollution is a cause for concern for advocates and public-health experts alike, who note that Philadelphia has one of the highest rates of childhood asthma in the nation. Dr. Marilyn Howarth of the University of Pennsylvania\'s Center of Excellence in Environmental Toxicology said the asthma rate of about 26 percent among kids in some of the city\'s poorest neighborhoods is three times the national average.</blockquote>\r\nThere\'s more.\r\n<blockquote>\"The refinery has traditionally contributed a great deal of pollution to the Philadelphia region, and as the refinery operations increase . . . you can only reasonably expect these emissions to increase,\" Howarth said. The Philadelphia region currently fails to meet federal clean-air standards for ozone and small-particulate matter, two crucial pollution yardsticks.</blockquote>\r\nIt\'s even worse then that.\r\n<blockquote>An EPA analysis of South Philadelphia toxic pollution released last fall found that the vast majority of emissions in the neighborhood came from the refinery and that 11 percent - nearly 40 tons - were known carcinogens, largely benzene. The two biggest sources - roughly two-thirds of the total - were sulfuric acid and hydrogen cyanide.\r\n\r\n\"Those are acids,\" said Howarth of the sulfur-laced emissions, \"and they are very strong pollutants. They may not cause cancer, but they certainly contribute to asthma and would irritate the airways for people with chronic pulmonary disease.\"</blockquote>\r\nSo basically it\'s a pretty clear connection between having a refinery in our city and not having acceptable clean air, having huge rates of asthma, significant risks to children and the elderly and infirm especially and increased risks of cancer.\r\n\r\nWant to know how many jobs we get for all that?  845.  To put that into perspective TWU Local 234 is just one of 17 unions with SEPTA provides over 5000 jobs alone.\r\n\r\nThe article also quotes the man who is profiting vastly from endangering and harming so many (and who does not live near his refinery) Phil Rinaldi, CEO of Philadelphia Energy Solutions which runs the refinery.  He is sure that opposition to an energy hub in Philadelphia is rooted in \"naivete\" and that he clearly believes that society cannot endure without burning fossil fuels.\r\n\r\nHowever the actual truth is that society cannot operate for much longer <a href=\"http://www.skepticalscience.com/\">burning fossil fuels like we are now</a>, and the time for when this must end is shorter then most people realize.   This makes any further investment like pipelines and new refineries a terrible short sighted idea even ignoring the terrible health effects they clearly have.  Mr Rinaldi will likely deny this as long as he possibly can, however he is the one who is naive if he thinks Philadelphians will let him pollute our city and our bodies so he can become unimaginably wealthy in the process without a fight.  A really big fight.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','845 jobs vs all of our lungs and the future of our city, world','','publish','open','open','','845-jobs-vs-all-of-our-lungs-and-the-future-of-our-city-world','','','2015-05-14 01:54:16','2015-05-14 01:54:16','',0,'http://brightphillyfuture.bowersad.com/?p=214',0,'post','',0),(215,1,'2015-05-10 02:36:01','2015-05-10 02:36:01','','0413_PXREFI13_1024_2','','inherit','open','open','','0413_pxrefi13_1024_2','','','2015-05-10 02:36:01','2015-05-10 02:36:01','',214,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/0413_PXREFI13_1024_2.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(218,1,'2015-05-10 03:11:29','2015-05-10 03:11:29','','Philadelphia1973_01_2000','','inherit','open','open','','philadelphia1973_01_2000','','','2015-05-10 03:11:29','2015-05-10 03:11:29','',0,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Philadelphia1973_01_2000.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(219,1,'2015-05-12 01:57:41','2015-05-12 01:57:41',' ','','','publish','open','open','','219','','','2015-05-13 20:49:16','2015-05-13 20:49:16','',31,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/index.php/2015/05/12/219/',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(220,1,'2015-05-12 01:57:41','2015-05-12 01:57:41',' ','','','publish','open','open','','220','','','2015-05-13 20:49:16','2015-05-13 20:49:16','',24,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/index.php/2015/05/12/220/',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(221,1,'2015-05-12 01:57:41','2015-05-12 01:57:41',' ','','','publish','open','open','','221','','','2015-05-13 20:49:16','2015-05-13 20:49:16','',0,'http://bpf2.bowersad.com/index.php/2015/05/12/221/',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(222,1,'2015-05-12 01:57:41','2015-05-12 01:57:41','','Get Action, Be Sane','','publish','open','open','','get-action-be-sane','','','2015-05-12 01:57:41','2015-0